      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUNA MOON (8) is still a maiden after 13 runs but rarely far away, the latest filling a minor placing when third at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Sure to be about the mark. GO FORWARD BERNY (2) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish second, beaten 11 lengths (23.51) at this track in a Maiden over 401m. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Likely to be in the finish again. EXCITING FORTE (1) has an honest record despite remaining a maiden after seven starts. Racing consistently finishing in the money the last three starts. Well placed and gets her chance. OUR LITTLE SUZIE (7) can sneak into the finish.",
